
[1]testing

   TEST'ING, ppr. [from test.] Trying for proof; proving by a standard or
   by experiment.

   A plan for testing alkalies--

                  TEST'ING, n. The act of trying for proof.

   1. In metallurgy, the operation of refining large quantities of gold or
   silver by means of lead, in the vessel called a test. In this process,
   the extraneous matter is vitrified, scarified or destroyed, and the
   metal left pure. This operation is performed in the manner of
   cupellation.
